article.headline: E. Michigan 89, Buffalo 76
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. (AP) -- Carlos Medlock scored a career-high 26 points and Jesse Bunkley added 15 Sunday to lift Eastern Michigan to an 89-76 victory over Buffalo. The win snapped a three-game losing streak for the Eagles (8-12, 3-4 Mid-American Conference). The 89 points were the most scored all season by Eastern Michigan and the most since scoring 89 against Cleveland State on Dec. 23, 2004. Eric Moore had 22 points and Yassin Idbihi and Max Boudreau each added 11 to lead the Bulls (9-11, 1-6). Buffalo has dropped its past four games and has lost its past five road contests. Eastern Michigan built on a 37-35 halftime lead by opening the second half with an 11-0 run. Idbihis two free throws with 14:33 remaining pulled Buffalo within 49-43. The Eagles responded by scoring 28 of the next 38 points to go up 77-53 with 6:25 left. The closest the Bulls got afterward was the final margin of victory. Eastern Michigan hit a season-best 52.7 percent (29-of-55) of its field-goal attempts, including 11 of 23 3-pointers. There were six lead changes and six ties in a first half in which the teams combined for 22 turnovers in the half, including 13 by Buffalo.
